5261 #endif
5262  }

3269  p = sweep_page->start; pend = p + sweep_page->total_slots;
3270  offset = p - NUM_IN_PAGE(p);
3271  bits = sweep_page->mark_bits;
3272 
3273  /* create guard : fill 1 out-of-range */
3274  bits[BITMAP_INDEX(p)] |= BITMAP_BIT(p)-1;
3275  bits[BITMAP_INDEX(pend)] |= ~(BITMAP_BIT(pend) - 1);
3276

3278  bitset = ~bits[i];
3279  if (bitset) {

3282  if (bitset & 1) {

6818  return attr; \

gc.c の 3451 行目に定義があります。

3452 {
3453  struct heap_page *sweep_page = heap->sweep_pages, *next;
3454  int unlink_limit = 3;
3455 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
3456  int need_pool = will_be_incremental_marking(objspace) ? TRUE : FALSE;
3457 
3458  gc_report(2, objspace, "gc_sweep_step (need_pool: %d)\n", need_pool);
3459 #else
3460  gc_report(2, objspace, "gc_sweep_step\n");
3461 #endif
3462 
3463  if (sweep_page == NULL) return FALSE;
3464 
3465 #if GC_ENABLE_LAZY_SWEEP
3466  gc_prof_sweep_timer_start(objspace);
3467 #endif
3468 
3469  while (sweep_page) {
3470  heap->sweep_pages = next = sweep_page->next;
3471  gc_page_sweep(objspace, heap, sweep_page);
3472 
3473  if (sweep_page->final_slots + sweep_page->free_slots == sweep_page->total_slots &&
3474  unlink_limit > 0) {
3475  unlink_limit--;
3476  /* there are no living objects -> move this page to tomb heap */
3477  heap_unlink_page(objspace, heap, sweep_page);
3478  heap_add_page(objspace, heap_tomb, sweep_page);
3479  }
3480  else if (sweep_page->free_slots > 0) {

1438

1441  if (page_body == 0) {
1442  rb_memerror();
1443  }
1444 
1445  /* assign heap_page entry */
1446  page = (struct heap_page *)calloc(1, sizeof(struct heap_page));
1447  if (page == 0) {
1448  aligned_free(page_body);
1449  rb_memerror();
1450  }
1451 
1452  page->body = page_body;
1453 
1454  /* setup heap_pages_sorted */
1455  lo = 0;
1456  hi = heap_allocated_pages;
1457  while (lo < hi) {
1458  struct heap_page *mid_page;
1459 
1460  mid = (lo + hi) / 2;
1461  mid_page = heap_pages_sorted[mid];
1462  if (mid_page->body < page_body) {
1463  lo = mid + 1;
1464  }
1465  else if (mid_page->body > page_body) {
1466  hi = mid;
1467  }
1468  else {
1469  rb_bug("same heap page is allocated: %p at %"PRIuVALUE, (void *)page_body, (VALUE)mid);
1470  }
1471  }

1474  }

1477

1486  int delta = (int)(sizeof(RVALUE) - ((VALUE)start % sizeof(RVALUE)));

1488  limit = (HEAP_SIZE - (int)((VALUE)start - (VALUE)page_body))/(int)sizeof(RVALUE);
1489  }

2863 #define NUM2PTR(x) NUM2ULL(x)
2864 #endif
2865  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2866  VALUE ptr;
2867  void *p0;
2868 
2869  ptr = NUM2PTR(objid);
2870  p0 = (void *)ptr;
2871 
2872  if (ptr == Qtrue) return Qtrue;
2873  if (ptr == Qfalse) return Qfalse;
2874  if (ptr == Qnil) return Qnil;
2875  if (FIXNUM_P(ptr)) return (VALUE)ptr;
2876  if (FLONUM_P(ptr)) return (VALUE)ptr;
2877  ptr = obj_id_to_ref(objid);
2878 
2879  if ((ptr % sizeof(RVALUE)) == (4 << 2)) {
2880  ID symid = ptr / sizeof(RVALUE);
2881  if (rb_id2str(symid) == 0)
2882  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "%p is not symbol id value", p0);
2883  return ID2SYM(symid);
2884  }
2885 
2886  if (!is_id_value(objspace, ptr)) {
2887  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "%p is not id value", p0);
2888  }
2889  if (!is_live_object(objspace, ptr)) {
2890  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "%p is recycled object", p0);
2891  }
2892  if (RBASIC(ptr)->klass == 0) {
2893  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "%p is internal object", p0);
2894  }
2895  return (VALUE)ptr;
2896 }

2210  while (0 < i && last_body < heap_pages_sorted[i-1]->body) i--;
2211  while (i < heap_allocated_pages && heap_pages_sorted[i]->body <= last_body) i++;
2212  if (heap_allocated_pages <= i) break;
2213 
2214  page = heap_pages_sorted[i];
2215  last_body = page->body;
2216 
2217  pstart = page->start;
2218  pend = pstart + page->total_slots;
2219 
2220  if ((*args->callback)(pstart, pend, sizeof(RVALUE), args->data)) {
2221  break;
2222  }
2223  }
2224 
2225  return Qnil;
2226 }

2925 {
2926  /*
2927  * 32-bit VALUE space
2928  * MSB ------------------------ LSB
2929  * false 00000000000000000000000000000000
2930  * true 00000000000000000000000000000010
2931  * nil 00000000000000000000000000000100
2932  * undef 00000000000000000000000000000110
2933  * symbol ssssssssssssssssssssssss00001110
2934  * object oooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo00 = 0 (mod sizeof(RVALUE))
2935  * fixnum fffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff1
2936  *
2937  * object_id space
2938  * LSB
2939  * false 00000000000000000000000000000000
2940  * true 00000000000000000000000000000010
2941  * nil 00000000000000000000000000000100
2942  * undef 00000000000000000000000000000110
2943  * symbol 000SSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS0 S...S % A = 4 (S...S = s...s * A + 4)
2944  * object oooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo0 o...o % A = 0
2945  * fixnum fffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff1 bignum if required
2946  *
2947  * where A = sizeof(RVALUE)/4
2948  *
2949  * sizeof(RVALUE) is
2950  * 20 if 32-bit, double is 4-byte aligned
2951  * 24 if 32-bit, double is 8-byte aligned
2952  * 40 if 64-bit
2953  */
2954  if (STATIC_SYM_P(obj)) {
2955  return (SYM2ID(obj) * sizeof(RVALUE) + (4 << 2)) | FIXNUM_FLAG;
2956  }
2957  else if (FLONUM_P(obj)) {
2958 #if SIZEOF_LONG == SIZEOF_VOIDP
2959  return LONG2NUM((SIGNED_VALUE)obj);
2960 #else
2961  return LL2NUM((SIGNED_VALUE)obj);
2962 #endif
2963  }
2964  else if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(obj)) {
2965  return LONG2NUM((SIGNED_VALUE)obj);
2966  }
2967  return nonspecial_obj_id(obj);
2968 }
